Introduction¶

Dataset Description¶

This data set contains information about 10,000 movies collected from The Movie Database (TMDb), including user ratings and revenue

Questions for Analysis¶

  • Q1 : What effect does the popularity of a movie have on revenue generation?

  • Q2 : Which of the casts have the most popularity?

  • Q3 : Who among the casts generated the most revenue?

  • Q4 : What are the leading movies based on revenue and budget?

Exploratory Data Analysis¶

Research Question 1 - What effect does the popularity of a movie have on revenue generation?¶

We seek to find out how the popularity index in turn affects the revenue generated. We seek to further explore to see the relation between popularity as against revenue?

Defining a custom function to plot the graphs¶

In [43]:
def plot_bargraph(x,y,title,xlabel,ylabel):
    plt.figure(figsize=[12,8])
    sns.barplot(x=x,y=y);
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel(xlabel)
    plt.ylabel(ylabel)
    plt.show()

Research Question 2 - Which of the casts have the most popularity?¶

I seek to find out the top 10 cast with high popularity

From the dataset I observed there are a lot of different casts based on each movie.

From the list of cast I would like to investigate and find out who has the most popularity. Since there are a large number of casts to deal with in order to avoid duplication we would have to explode the cast index

In [61]:
# Exploding a dataset helps to transform each element of list-like to a row, replicating the index values.

castdf=df.assign(cast=df['cast'].str.split('|')).explode('cast')
In [41]:
rank_by_cast=castdf.groupby('cast',as_index=False)['popularity'].mean()
In [42]:
# We would further rank the actors since our focus will be on the top 10 with huge popularity

top_10=rank_by_cast.sort_values(by='popularity',ascending=False).head(10)

Conclusions¶

  • Popularity has an effect on the revenue that would be generated from movies. As popularity soars, revenue also increases along with it
  • Cast with a good amount of popularity also plays a crucial role. Once a cast with a huge popularity is onboarded in translates in the revenue generated.
  • Revenue and budget are important parameters to pay attention to in movies. It has a bearing on the outcome of the movie and must be given nuch attention.

Limitations¶

  • Visualization was a problem due to missing values in some of the columns. For example, in considering cast, it had 76 values which were missing. This did not enable visualization to be carried out
